<p />
<font color="#808080"> <ul>
<li> Layout the table of contents before you start writing the document if possible.
</li> <li> The purpose of the table of contents is to provide a good overview about the installation procedure. The reader should be able to identify major steps by reading the table of contents.
</li> <li> The table of contents also provides quick navigation within the document. Please use expressive names for the individual headings that allow readers to determine what a specific section is about.
</li> <li> Adjust the <code>depth</code> such that overview and navigation are served best.
</li> <li> Example: <a href="/bin/view/Trash/ReleaseDocumentationComputeElementInstall" class="twikiLink">Compute Element Installation Guide</a>
</li> <li> All headings start at Level1 "+".
</li> <li> The main heading is to be excluded from the table of contents.
</li></ul> 
</font>
<p />
<font color="#808080">
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd>  The following sections are a super set for all the different sections found in various installation documents. Particular sections may not be helpful for the installation document you are writing and may be excluded.
</dd></dl> 
</font>
<p />
<h1><a name="2_About_this_Document"></a> 2  About this Document </h1>
<font color="#808080">  Example: </font> <br />    
Here we describe how to install and configure the %GLOSSARY_RSV% service on your Linux machine. 
This document is intended for site administrators who want to use these RSV to monitor their systems. 
It explains how to install and configure the RSV service and the default probes. 
For documents on specific probes or on how to write your own probes please check the <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/DocInstallTemplate#References" class="twikiCurrentTopicLink twikiAnchorLink">References section</a>.
<p />
Please consult the <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/DocFormattingRules#Presenting_the_Unix_Command_Line" class="twikiAnchorLink">formatting rules for the command line</a> and define your own variables used here.
<p />
</font>
<p />
<img width="16" alt="hand" align="top" src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/hand.gif" height="16" border="0" /> This document is intended for System Administrators that are installing ...
<p />
<font color="#808080"> <ul>
<li> Include a brief description about this document. Questions that this section should answer are:
</li> <li> Who is the target audience for the document (a system administrator, a grid user, a student, ...)?
</li> <li> What is the main goal of the document or what will the reader have accomplished when having read it?
</li> <li> If applicable, what does the document not accomplish? For instance an installation document for a service does not explain the client tools for it.    
</li> <li> If useful, include a brief descriptions of conventions used in the document, like so:
</li></ul> 
</font>
<p />
on    
on    
<p />
<font color="#808080">
Include useful variable definitions inside an HTML comment here, for example:
<pre>
&#60;!-- Variables used in this Document 
   &#42; Local BESTMAN &#61; !BeStMan
   &#42; Local UCL&#95;USER &#61; daemon
   &#42; Local UCL&#95;CWD  &#61; /opt/osg-&#37;VERSION&#37;
   &#42; Local UCL&#95;HOST &#61; host
--&#62;
</pre>
</font>
<h1><a name="3_Applicable_Versions_Optional"></a> 3  Applicable Versions (Optional) </h1>
<p />
<font color="#808080">
In case the procedure differs significantly for different versions of the OSG or VDT, please include this section.
</font>
<p />
The applicable software versions for this document are <font color="#ff0000">OSG Version &gt;= x.y</font> and <font color="#ff0000">VDT Version &gt;= a.b</font>.
<p />
<h1><a name="4_Introduction_Optional"></a> 4  Introduction (Optional) </h1>
<p />
<font color="#808080">
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd>  This section may sometimes be called differently, such as "About Compute Element Services".
</dd></dl> 
<p />
This optional section may contain a brief technical description. It may explain what the purpose of the installed software is and when it is needed. It should help the reader make a decision if the content of the document is relevant for him. It may also explain terms being used throughout the document complete with links to the Glossary if possible. See for example  the introduction of the <a href="/bin/view/Trash/ReleaseDocumentationWorkerNodeClient#What_is_the_Worker_Node_Client_a" class="twikiAnchorLink">Worker Node Client</a>.
<p />
</font>
<p />
<h1><a name="5_Engineering_Considerations_Opt"></a> 5  Engineering Considerations (Optional) </h1>
<p />
<font color="#808080">
Please provide this section if an extensive amount of planning is required before the installation can proceed. This could be installations that require services and/or software to be installed on several machines.
</font>
<p />
<h1><a name="6_Requirements"></a> 6  Requirements </h1>
<font color="#808080">
This section serves as a possible early exit point for readers of the document. It must list all requirements that have to be met in order for a typical installation to succeed. All tools mentioned must be linked. All terminologies used should be linked to the Glossary explaining them.  The Requirements are broken into 4 subsections with the following formatting (example):
</font>
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="6_1_Host_and_OS"></a> 6.1  Host and OS </span></h2> <ul>
<li> A host to install the RSV Service (Can be the CE or a separate, standalone computer)
</li> <li> OS is Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5, 6, 7, and variants (see <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/Release3/SupportedOperatingSystems" class="twikiLink">details...</a>). 
</li> <li> Root access
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="6_2_Users"></a> 6.2  Users </span></h2>
The RSV installation will create two users unless they are already created.
<p />
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" class="twikinetWrapperTable" rules="none">
