</font>
<p />
In the next step we will configure the service using following steps:
<p /> <ol>
<li> edit this file
</li> <li> open that firewall port
</li> <li> ...
</li></ol> 
<p />
<font color="#808080">
Steps listed as part of the numbered list above should have their own sub-section inside this section. For example:
</font>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="8_1_1st_Step_of_the_Configuratio"></a> 8.1  &lt;1st Step of the Configuration Procedure&gt; </span></h2>
<p />
<font color="#808080">
The procedure may require the reader to edit configuration files. We will use a CSS class named <em>file</em> to render a yellow box around the content ( or parts of it ) of the file:
<p />
<pre>&#60;pre class&#61;&#34;file&#34;&#62;
Config file line a
Config file line b
&#60;/pre&#62;</pre>
<p />
</font>
<p />
<pre class="file">
Config file line a
Config file line b
</pre>
<p />
<font color="#808080">
<p /> <dl>
<dt> <img src="/twiki/pub/TWiki/TWikiDocGraphics/help.gif" alt="HELP" title="HELP" width="16" height="16" border="0" />     <strong><font color="#ff0000"> NOTE </font></strong> </dt><dd>  For more information <a href="/bin/view/Documentation/DocFormattingRules#Presenting_File_Content" class="twikiAnchorLink">see here</a>.
</dd></dl> 
</font>
